<div class="shoe" id="nike-vomero-premium">
  <h2>Nike Vomero Premium <span class="badge">On Display</span></h2>
  <div class="meta"><span class="price">$180</span> <span class="rating">Rating: 4.5/5</span></div>
  <p class="specs">Weight: 10.6 oz &bull; Cushion: High &bull; Cut: Low &bull; Drop: 10mm &bull; Support: Neutral &bull; Surface: Road</p>
  <p>The Nike Vomero Premium is Nike's most cushioned road running shoe ever — a bold, anti-gravity daily trainer designed for high-mileage athletes who want maximum impact protection without sacrificing feel. It features a towering 55mm heel stack height, combining a full-length ZoomX foam midsole with two exposed Air Zoom units — one in the heel and one in the forefoot — borrowed directly from Nike's MaxFly and Victory track spikes. The result is a uniquely springy, plush ride that rolls through each stride with surprising momentum. Worn by Faith Kipyegon during her Breaking4 training, the Vomero Premium is Nike's answer for elite marathon runners who want a true recovery trainer that still feels alive underfoot. The wide, stable platform prevents wobble despite all that foam, and the exaggerated "AIR" branding on the heel is a deliberate nod to the 1996 Air More Uptempo. Best for: recovery runs, easy-pace long runs, and high-mileage days when your legs need a break. Key specs: 55mm heel stack, ZoomX + dual Air Zoom units, 10.6 oz, 10mm drop, neutral, road.</p>
  
</div>

<div class="shoe" id="nike-vomero-plus">
  <h2>Nike Vomero Plus <span class="badge">On Display</span></h2>
  <div class="meta"><span class="price">$180</span> <span class="rating">Rating: 4.4/5</span></div>
  <p class="specs">Weight: 10.9 oz &bull; Cushion: High &bull; Cut: Low &bull; Drop: 10mm &bull; Support: Neutral &bull; Surface: Road</p>
  <p>The Nike Vomero Plus sits one step below the Vomero Premium in Nike's max-cushion lineup but is no less impressive. It features a full-length ZoomX midsole at a 45mm stack height, offering a softer, lighter, and more responsive ride than the standard Vomero 18. Without the weight of the dual Air Zoom units, the Vomero Plus feels slightly more agile and is a better everyday option for runners who want extreme cushion without the heft of the Premium. Olympic silver medalist Jess Hull described it as "a great introductory shoe for a smooth, responsive and well-cushioned ride at a wide range of paces." Great for daily mileage, easy runs, and runners stepping into max-cushion territory. Key specs: 45mm stack, full ZoomX midsole, 10.9 oz, 10mm drop, neutral, road.</p>
  
</div>

<div class="shoe" id="nike-pegasus-premium">
  <h2>Nike Pegasus Premium <span class="badge">On Display</span></h2>
  <div class="meta"><span class="price">$160</span> <span class="rating">Rating: 4.5/5</span></div>
  <p class="specs">Weight: 10.2 oz &bull; Cushion: Moderate &bull; Cut: Low &bull; Drop: 10mm &bull; Support: Neutral &bull; Surface: Road</p>
  <p>The Nike Pegasus Premium is the elevated version of Nike's iconic everyday workhorse, built for runners who want the familiar Pegasus ride with significantly more cushioning and energy return. It features a full-length Air Zoom Strobel unit for a snappy, responsive toe-off, plus a ZoomX foam midsole for a noticeably softer landing than the standard Pegasus 41. At 10.2 oz and a 10mm drop, it suits runners logging daily mileage across a range of paces — not just recovery jogs but moderate-effort runs and longer efforts. Key specs: Air Zoom Strobel + ZoomX, 10.2 oz, 10mm drop, moderate cushion, neutral, road.</p>
  
</div>

<div class="shoe" id="hoka-bondi-9">
  <h2>HOKA Bondi 9 <span class="badge">On Display</span></h2>
  <div class="meta"><span class="price">$165</span> <span class="rating">Rating: 4.6/5</span></div>
  <p class="specs">Weight: 9.4 oz &bull; Cushion: Max &bull; Cut: Low &bull; Drop: 4mm &bull; Support: Neutral &bull; Surface: Road</p>
  <p>The HOKA Bondi 9 is HOKA's flagship max-cushion daily trainer, completely overhauled for 2025. The biggest upgrade is an all-new supercritical EVA foam midsole — a significant step up from the compressed EVA of previous models — delivering a noticeably more responsive and bouncy ride while retaining the deep, forgiving cushion the Bondi is known for. Stack height increased to 43mm heel / 38mm forefoot, and HOKA added an Active Foot Frame for improved rearfoot stability. The upper features 55% recycled polyester, a 3D molded collar for ankle comfort, and structured knit with zonal breathability. MetaRocker geometry creates a smooth, rolling heel-to-toe transition that reduces calf fatigue on long runs or long days on your feet. Earned the APMA Seal of Acceptance. Best for: easy runs, recovery days, long walks, and anyone who spends hours on hard surfaces. Key specs: supercritical EVA, 43/38mm stack, 9.4 oz (women's), 5mm drop, max cushion, neutral, road.</p>
  
</div>

<div class="shoe" id="on-cloud-monster-3">
  <h2>On Cloud Monster 3 <span class="badge">On Display</span></h2>
